# 🖥️ **Windows Performance Tune-Up Lab Guide**

## 🎯 **Lab Overview**
This lab provides a step-by-step process to tune up and optimize a Windows computer without formatting. Students will learn how to improve system performance by removing unnecessary files, managing startup applications, and adjusting system settings.

## 📌 **Objectives**
- **Learn how to perform basic daily maintenance.**
- **Apply weekly and monthly optimization techniques.**
- **Understand long-term performance improvement strategies.**

## 🛠️ **Lab Tasks**

### ✅ **Daily Quick Maintenance**
- **Close unused apps and browser tabs.**
- **Open Task Manager (Ctrl + Shift + Esc). Check for unnecessary processes and end them.**
- **Save work and restart PC to refresh memory.**

### 🔄 **Weekly Maintenance**
- **Delete temporary files:**
  - Press **Win + R → type temp** → delete contents.
  - Press **Win + R → type %temp%** → delete contents.
  - Run **Disk Cleanup**: Press **Win**, search for **Disk Cleanup**, and select the drive to clean.
- **Manage startup apps:**
  - Open **Task Manager → Startup tab → Disable non-essential apps.**
- **Update Windows & apps:**
  - Go to **Start → Settings → Update & Security → Windows Update → Check for updates.**
- **Run malware scan:**
  - Open **Windows Security → Virus & Threat Protection → Quick Scan.**

### 📅 **Monthly Deep Tune-Up**
- **Optimize drives:**
  - Press **Win**, type **Defragment and Optimize Drives → Select drive → Optimize.**
  - For SSD, confirm TRIM is enabled: Open **Command Prompt → run** `fsutil behavior query DisableDeleteNotify`. Value **0** means TRIM is enabled.
- **Clean large files:**
  - Open **File Explorer → Downloads/Documents → Move old files to external drive or cloud.**
- **Update drivers:**
  - Press **Win + X → Device Manager → Right-click device → Update driver.**
- **Adjust performance settings:**
  - Press **Win + R → type sysdm.cpl → Advanced tab → Performance Settings → Adjust for best performance or leave default.**
- **Manage background apps:**
  - Go to **Settings → Apps → Installed Apps → Modify background permissions.**

### 🗓️ **Every 6 Months**
- **Clean physical hardware:**
  - Power down PC, clean dust from fans and vents.
- **Full malware scan:**
  - Open **Windows Security → Virus & Threat Protection → Full Scan.**
- **Review installed software:**
  - Go to **Settings → Apps → Uninstall unused applications.**

## ⚡ **Bonus (Optional Upgrades)**
- **Add more RAM** if system usage stays above 80%.
- **Replace HDD with SSD** for significant speed boost.
- **Use Windows Reset (without deleting files)** if issues persist.

## 📋 **Windows Performance Tune-Up Checklist**

### ✅ **Daily (Quick Habits)**
- [ ] **Close unused apps and browser tabs.**
- [ ] **Check Task Manager (Ctrl + Shift + Esc) if PC feels slow → end unneeded processes.**
- [ ] **Save work and restart PC once a day (refreshes memory).**

### 🔄 **Weekly (Light Maintenance)**
- [ ] **Delete temporary files:**
  - Run **Win + R → temp** and **%temp%** → delete contents.
  - Use **Storage Sense** or **cleanmgr.**
- [ ] **Check startup apps:** **Task Manager → Startup tab → keep only essentials.**
- [ ] **Update Windows & apps:** **Settings → Windows Update.**
- [ ] **Scan for malware:** Quick scan with **Windows Defender (or Malwarebytes).**

### 📅 **Monthly (Deep Tune-Up)**
- [ ] **Disk optimization:**
  - HDD → **Defragment & Optimize Drives.**
  - SSD → Confirm TRIM is enabled (`fsutil behavior query DisableDeleteNotify` should return 0).
- [ ] **Clean large files:** Move old downloads, videos, backups to external drive/cloud.
- [ ] **Check drivers:** Update **GPU, chipset, and network drivers.**
- [ ] **Performance settings:** Verify **Power Plan = Balanced or High performance.**
- [ ] **Background apps:** **Settings → Apps → Installed Apps → Background Permissions → set to Never for unused apps.**

### 🗓️ **Every 6 Months**
- [ ] **Dust cleanup:** Physically clean fans/vents to prevent overheating.
- [ ] **Full virus/malware scan.**
- [ ] **Review installed software → uninstall unused apps.**

### ⚡ **Bonus (When Needed)**
- **Add more RAM** if usage is always >80%.
- **Switch HDD → SSD** for a huge speed upgrade.
- **Reset Windows (without deleting files)** if performance still lags after all tune-ups.

## 📋 **Deliverables**
- **Document steps completed with screenshots.**
- **Submit a short reflection: Which optimization step improved performance the most?**

